 <!--121-->The Twilight World    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Bid around 3. It&#39;s not that important to start the game off. In someways it can help you if the other player starts. He has to go through your sites and it really helps this deck to get out the Ford of Bruinen, since all of the Nazgul. It wont be that hard to get out Aragorn anyways concedering that most people play with Prancing Pony.<br />
<br />
Take it slow at first and get prepared for the Balrog. Try and get out Hobbit Stealth before the Bridge and use Merry to avoid the Balrog. If that doesn&#39;t work than use Boromir with armor and hopefully some power boosters incase they have the two hand weapons for it. Use Aragorn for almost every thing else. The No Stanger to the Shadows should help limit your opponite on what he can do, that way you can forge ahead. The most important thing to remember is not to forget to heal your companions with Aragorn. This works to your advantage because there is so much healing in this deck all you really need the power-ups for are so that you can prevant your companions from being overwelmed, espicially Aragorn when he takes on more than one minion.<br />
<br />
As for the Shadow side all you really need to do is try and cause as much damage as you can. Don&#39;t concentrate to much on trying to overwelm your opponite. If it comes it comes.<br />
<br />
Overall, if you go through this strategy, you should have a pretty good chance at winning </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
